存在於空氣中慢生根瘤菌科的細菌''[[Afipia|Afipia]]''，以[[二甲基砜|二甲基砜]]為其碳來源<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2013/01/22/1212089110.full.pdf+html|title= Microbiome of the upper troposphere: Species composition and prevalence, effects of tropical storms, and atmospheric implications|author = Natasha DeLeon-Rodriguez, others ([http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2013/01/22/1212089110?tab=author-info full list])|date = December 19, 2012 (received for review July 15, 2012)|quote = This group [Afipia] is commonly found in aquatic environments and is known to use dimethyl sulfone (DMSO<small>2</small>) as a sole carbon source. DMSO<small>2</small> represents an intermediate of the oxidation of dimethyl sulfide (DMS), which is commonly found in the marine atmosphere|accessdate=2014-03-01 |language=en |page=5 }}</ref>。

